In my opinion, technology has made dating much more easier.  It is far easier to find people that share your interests and that would be willing to date you.  I have used dating apps and it has been a great experience.  Before dating apps, I found it pretty hard to meet people that I connected with.  After college, I moved to a town where I didn't know anyone.  I didn't have friends who could introduce me to new people.  I didn't have a job that introduced me to a lot of new people in my age group.   

Dating apps allowed me to find people who were ready to date and were also interested in me.  I have never been the type of person to randomly walk up to a stranger in public to try to kindle a romantic relationship.  I worried about whether they were interested in me.  I worried about whether they were even single and looking to date.  With online dating apps, I never had to worry about that.
